1
00:00:17,790 --> 00:00:19,320
I'm really upset.

2
00:00:20,230 --> 00:00:23,730
I don't have a problem with
accepting fair criticism.

3
00:00:25,060 --> 00:00:26,160
But they said they wouldn't
eat our macaroons...

4
00:00:26,160 --> 00:00:27,500
even if someone offered them money...

5
00:00:27,970 --> 00:00:29,740
and that they even got
stomachaches after eating them.

6
00:00:29,770 --> 00:00:32,220
How are we supposed to deal with such lies?

7
00:00:32,900 --> 00:00:34,950
Is it possible to sue the power blogger...

8
00:00:35,210 --> 00:00:37,660
and all the people that
left comments on the post?

9
00:00:37,680 --> 00:00:38,700
Of course.

10
00:00:39,040 --> 00:00:42,220
You can sue them for spreading
false information and slander.

11
00:00:42,510 --> 00:00:46,180
First, you should file a complaint.
And at the same time,

12
00:00:46,180 --> 00:00:48,870
you can also file a damage suit
against particular suspects.

13
00:00:49,190 --> 00:00:52,790
I have nightmares every single day.

14
00:00:52,860 --> 00:00:55,340
I've come to respect the celebrities...

15
00:00:55,590 --> 00:00:56,960
that I see on TV.

16
00:00:57,260 --> 00:01:00,230
I wonder how they manage to bear
with all the mean comments online.

17
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:06,800
By the way, your secretary
must really like macaroons.

18
00:01:10,610 --> 00:01:13,670
Send me screenshots of the comments
that you think can be a problem.

19
00:01:14,210 --> 00:01:16,460
I'll send you the petition as
soon as I'm done writing it.

20
00:01:16,480 --> 00:01:18,870
And if you're fine with that,
I'll go ahead with the suit.

21
00:01:18,950 --> 00:01:19,970
Okay.

22
00:01:26,790 --> 00:01:29,520
Thank you for buying me so many.

23
00:01:29,730 --> 00:01:33,130
Thanks to you,
I'll get to eat so many macaroons.

24
00:01:33,570 --> 00:01:37,620
No problem. You can eat them and
give me an objective opinion.

25
00:01:38,270 --> 00:01:41,300
See if they're bad enough for people
to make harsh comments about them.

26
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:46,670
Is that why you took me with you?
To make me taste the macaroons?

27
00:01:47,450 --> 00:01:50,440
Okay, sure. You can count on me.
I really love macaroons.

28
00:01:50,820 --> 00:01:52,720
But even if you like them that much,

29
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:55,450
do you really think you can eat
everything all by yourself?

30
00:01:55,450 --> 00:01:57,430
I'm not going to eat this all by myself.

31
00:01:57,820 --> 00:02:01,640
I'm only going to have one and share
the rest with everyone at the firm.

32
00:02:02,030 --> 00:02:03,970
I'm a loyal woman, you know.

33
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:05,360
Not only are you loyal,

34
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:08,120
but you're also attractive
and warm-hearted.

35
00:02:10,500 --> 00:02:11,520
Who are you?

36
00:02:12,870 --> 00:02:15,260
Mr. Kwon I know isn't
capable of being sweet.

37
00:02:16,370 --> 00:02:17,430
Who are you?

38
00:02:20,010 --> 00:02:21,340
I'm kidding.

39
00:02:22,480 --> 00:02:25,480
I didn't know you could
make such sweet comments,

40
00:02:25,480 --> 00:02:26,880
so I couldn't believe what I just heard.

41
00:02:26,950 --> 00:02:30,520
From now on, you should say
that kind of stuff more often.

42
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:31,540
Okay.

43
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:33,830
Aren't you going to eat one?

44
00:02:33,830 --> 00:02:34,540
Yes.

45
00:02:35,330 --> 00:02:36,350
Which one should I eat?

46
00:02:36,390 --> 00:02:38,710
The names of the macaroons
are really interesting.

47
00:02:38,730 --> 00:02:42,070
"A taste I cannot stop craving,
mocha macaroon".

48
00:02:42,130 --> 00:02:44,960
"Tasty and pretty, chocolate macaroon".

49
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:48,400
"A taste that calls for
a kiss, mint macaroon".

50
00:02:49,370 --> 00:02:52,710
I wonder what kind of
taste calls for a kiss.

51
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:12,000
- We're back.
- Hello.

52
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:13,050
Hello.

53
00:03:14,670 --> 00:03:16,130
Ta-da.

54
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:19,030
Mr. Kwon bought macaroons for us.

55
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:22,070
- They look so delicious.
- You can take whatever you want.

56
00:03:22,070 --> 00:03:24,040
I want the strawberry flavored one.

57
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:25,470
I want the chocolate flavored one.

58
00:03:25,910 --> 00:03:29,830
I'm going to have the Earl Grey flavor.

59
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:32,230
Yun Seo, you should have this one.

60
00:03:32,420 --> 00:03:34,740
"A taste that calls for
a kiss, mint macaroon".

61
00:03:36,490 --> 00:03:40,210
Goodness, I don't want to kiss anyone.

62
00:03:40,290 --> 00:03:42,370
- My goodness.
- What?

63
00:03:53,540 --> 00:03:55,940
Mr. Kwon, do you need anything?

64
00:03:55,940 --> 00:03:57,850
From now on, I'm not going to ask.

65
00:03:58,410 --> 00:04:01,060
What? What do you mean?

66
00:04:02,550 --> 00:04:04,050
You said I shouldn't ask.

67
00:04:09,050 --> 00:04:10,830
You're not going to ask?

68
00:04:11,860 --> 00:04:12,980
Here?

69
00:04:14,090 --> 00:04:15,110
That's right.

70
00:04:18,330 --> 00:04:20,980
I always checked if you delivered
the sentencing properly.

71
00:04:21,130 --> 00:04:23,860
but I won't anymore since
you always do a good job.

72
00:04:27,310 --> 00:04:29,960
Gosh, I'm tired. I need a cup of coffee.

73
00:04:34,210 --> 00:04:37,180
You're insane! Even if it was that good...

74
00:04:37,180 --> 00:04:40,250
What are you talking about?
What do you mean it was good?

75
00:04:41,190 --> 00:04:43,510
Well, I can't say that it wasn't.

76
00:04:45,090 --> 00:04:46,800
Darn it! Whatever.

77
00:04:47,430 --> 00:04:50,050
This is a sacred workplace.
Yun Seo, please.

78
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,430
Just focus on your work.

79
00:04:52,430 --> 00:04:54,470
Focus. Concentrate!

80
00:05:00,140 --> 00:05:02,110
Here's the material you asked for.

81
00:05:02,110 --> 00:05:03,160
Thanks.

82
00:05:03,710 --> 00:05:05,750
It's just like the owner said.

83
00:05:06,380 --> 00:05:08,250
The hate comments are unbelievable.

84
00:05:08,950 --> 00:05:11,200
The macaroons were of decent quality,

85
00:05:11,420 --> 00:05:14,620
but some spoke ill of it just
because they were angry.

86
00:05:14,620 --> 00:05:17,190
Some even wrote lies about how...

87
00:05:17,190 --> 00:05:18,720
he didn't work at a German bakery.

88
00:05:19,320 --> 00:05:21,810
He must be truly upset over this.

89
00:05:22,890 --> 00:05:26,170
Many wrote hate comments
about me back in the day,

90
00:05:26,260 --> 00:05:28,270
so I know how he feels.

91
00:05:31,440 --> 00:05:34,200
I tell myself hundreds
and thousands of times...

92
00:05:34,270 --> 00:05:36,280
to not care and to be strong and brave.

93
00:05:37,910 --> 00:05:41,450
However, some comments
stabbed me in the heart.

94
00:05:42,580 --> 00:05:44,320
I still haven't forgotten about them,

95
00:05:44,650 --> 00:05:46,900
and where they stabbed me
sting from time to time.

96
00:05:47,850 --> 00:05:49,180
Why didn't you sue them?

97
00:05:50,050 --> 00:05:52,370
Well, I did.

98
00:05:53,860 --> 00:05:57,100
I met them, and
they were either students...

99
00:05:57,530 --> 00:05:59,540
or a mother and father with children.

100
00:05:59,860 --> 00:06:01,570
Punishing them didn't seem right.

101
00:06:03,100 --> 00:06:07,120
I dropped the charges after they
promised not to do it again.

102
00:06:09,570 --> 00:06:10,630
The phone's ringing.

103
00:06:13,080 --> 00:06:14,920
Just how brutal were the hate comments?

104
00:06:18,350 --> 00:06:20,230
(Oh Yun Seo)

105
00:06:21,090 --> 00:06:24,590
("Top Celebrity Oh Yun Seo
Questioned on Drug Use")

106
00:06:29,830 --> 00:06:30,950
I'm pressing charges.

107
00:06:32,260 --> 00:06:33,770
Sorry? On what?

108
00:06:33,770 --> 00:06:36,300
I looked up the comments written about you.

109
00:06:36,300 --> 00:06:38,720
These aren't just hate comments.
It's a crime.

110
00:06:38,870 --> 00:06:41,210
They must know what they did...

111
00:06:41,210 --> 00:06:43,210
by writing such malicious things.

112
00:06:43,210 --> 00:06:45,220
Also, they should be severely punished.

113
00:06:45,310 --> 00:06:46,470
So right this instant...

114
00:06:49,210 --> 00:06:52,140
Why are you laughing when I'm dead serious?

115
00:06:53,990 --> 00:06:55,250
I'm happy, that's why.

116
00:06:55,950 --> 00:06:56,830
What?

117
00:06:57,650 --> 00:06:58,880
What are you happy about?

118
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:01,630
How could I not be?

119
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:04,340
You rarely show emotions.

120
00:07:07,070 --> 00:07:08,910
This is how you normally are,

121
00:07:09,030 --> 00:07:11,350
but you're outraged because
of what happened to me...

122
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:13,200
as if it happened to you.

123
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:16,020
From now on,
what's your business is my business.

124
00:07:25,280 --> 00:07:27,130
I'm really fine.

125
00:07:27,750 --> 00:07:29,350
Thank you for caring though.

126
00:07:34,130 --> 00:07:35,460
Ms. Oh, how about we go to dinner...

127
00:07:37,330 --> 00:07:38,420
What?

128
00:07:39,660 --> 00:07:41,920
Okay, fine. I got it!

129
00:07:42,070 --> 00:07:44,590
Precedents? I'll look them up for you!

130
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:48,940
Did you really need to grill me about them?

131
00:07:50,380 --> 00:07:53,240
My timing was awful, wasn't it?

132
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:55,600
I'll let you get back to your business.

133
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:01,190
Mr. Kwon, are you all right?

134
00:08:01,190 --> 00:08:04,220
- Yes, I'm fine.
- I'm sorry.

135
00:08:04,890 --> 00:08:07,110
I improvised so that we
wouldn't get caught.

136
00:08:07,630 --> 00:08:09,190
I even acted a little.

137
00:08:10,090 --> 00:08:13,220
Right. I applaud your fast-thinking.

138
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:15,750
You're quite strong too.

139
00:08:32,250 --> 00:08:35,350
Actors seem like they live glamorous lives,

140
00:08:35,750 --> 00:08:37,460
but it must be a lot of stress.

141
00:08:37,860 --> 00:08:40,950
Awful comments must be considered
an occupational hazard.

142
00:08:43,830 --> 00:08:47,680
Still, I had more fun moments though.

143
00:08:49,270 --> 00:08:52,160
An exciting script would
make my heart thump.

144
00:08:53,140 --> 00:08:56,580
Being on a busy set made
me feel like I'm alive.

145
00:08:57,580 --> 00:09:00,030
When my work is received well,

146
00:09:00,380 --> 00:09:01,640
I feel gratified.

147
00:09:01,710 --> 00:09:04,580
Most of my memories are of fun incidents.

148
00:09:06,450 --> 00:09:09,550
There was a show I worked
on called "Signal".

149
00:09:10,150 --> 00:09:11,860
That's the one I remember the most.

150
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:15,530
I had to bring out a new side
that was hidden within me.

151
00:09:16,530 --> 00:09:19,220
It must be memorable because
it was a challenge.

152
00:09:22,630 --> 00:09:24,920
I liked every project I worked on though.

153
00:09:25,270 --> 00:09:28,400
However, you wouldn't know
since you never watched any.

154
00:09:30,210 --> 00:09:31,230
Well...

155
00:09:33,010 --> 00:09:34,410
Sorry, I need to take this call.

156
00:09:37,020 --> 00:09:38,210
Yes, this is Kwon Jung Rok.

157
00:09:38,950 --> 00:09:41,150
Sure. I'm outside right now,

158
00:09:41,150 --> 00:09:43,950
but I'll send you the document
as soon as I get back.

159
00:09:44,820 --> 00:09:46,390
Sure, of course.

160
00:09:46,890 --> 00:09:47,910
Take care.

161
00:09:50,190 --> 00:09:52,880
Do you need to head back to the office?

162
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:56,430
- Yes.
- Then why did you leave?

163
00:09:58,400 --> 00:10:00,480
I wanted to give you a ride home.

164
00:10:03,340 --> 00:10:04,540
Really?

165
00:10:05,380 --> 00:10:06,870
You didn't have to.

166
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:12,420
This must be why people
get into relationships.

167
00:10:12,420 --> 00:10:15,350
I have someone who cares about me
and looks out for me.

168
00:10:15,990 --> 00:10:17,190
It's nice.

169
00:10:40,110 --> 00:10:43,170
There was a show I worked
on called "Signal".

170
00:10:43,850 --> 00:10:45,860
That's the one I remember the most.

171
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:49,010
However, you wouldn't know
since you never watched any.

172
00:10:59,060 --> 00:11:01,670
"A woman becomes an insurance planner..."

173
00:11:01,670 --> 00:11:03,840
"at Signal Insurance."

174
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:06,090
"She turns her life around..."

175
00:11:06,640 --> 00:11:08,680
"after becoming a top salesperson."

176
00:11:13,540 --> 00:11:14,630
Detective Lee?

177
00:11:15,310 --> 00:11:17,500
Just what on earth happened...

178
00:11:17,780 --> 00:11:19,210
in 1997?

179
00:11:19,620 --> 00:11:21,120
I know though.

180
00:11:22,190 --> 00:11:25,080
You had your appendix removed.

181
00:11:25,690 --> 00:11:27,890
However, your insurance didn't cover any...

182
00:11:27,890 --> 00:11:29,770
of your actual expenses.

183
00:11:30,430 --> 00:11:33,010
Life doesn't end at 60.

184
00:11:33,160 --> 00:11:36,740
You can change your future.

185
00:11:37,470 --> 00:11:39,340
Please don't give up!

186
00:11:47,850 --> 00:11:50,330
How could you cheat on me?

187
00:11:51,020 --> 00:11:53,650
How can you love two women...

188
00:11:53,650 --> 00:11:55,430
with only one heart?

189
00:11:58,570 --> 00:12:03,820
♫ <i>You don't need to smile anymore</i> ♫

190
00:12:05,460 --> 00:12:11,260
♫ <i>Your eyes and lips</i> ♫

191
00:12:12,300 --> 00:12:17,010
♫ <i>They say it all</i> ♫

192
00:12:17,010 --> 00:12:23,680
(Soft but rich, the sip that fills me up)

193
00:12:25,510 --> 00:12:32,830
♫ <i>Your pillow that was always wet</i> ♫

194
00:12:32,830 --> 00:12:38,380
♫ <i>Finally, it'll be dry</i> ♫

195
00:12:38,380 --> 00:12:42,030
♫ <i>We went through so much</i> ♫

196
00:12:42,100 --> 00:12:43,120
I miss her.

197
00:12:45,900 --> 00:12:50,540
♫ <i>We fought so much</i> ♫

198
00:12:50,540 --> 00:12:55,680
♫ <i>We made up so many times</i> ♫

199
00:12:55,700 --> 00:13:02,500
♫ <i>Now we don't have to stay up
at night worrying anymore</i> ♫

200
00:13:02,540 --> 00:13:08,210
♫ <i>Now have a peaceful, good night</i> ♫

201
00:13:09,360 --> 00:13:11,030
You're more surprised than
I expected you to be.

202
00:13:11,230 --> 00:13:14,260
Although, that's the reason
why I didn't call ahead.

203
00:13:16,100 --> 00:13:17,570
What are you doing here at this hour?

204
00:13:18,070 --> 00:13:19,300
Ta-da.

205
00:13:19,300 --> 00:13:22,580
I come bearing a late-night snack.

206
00:13:23,410 --> 00:13:25,830
You ought to be slightly hungry by now,

207
00:13:26,640 --> 00:13:29,770
and I wanted to see how you
were doing without me.

208
00:13:30,920 --> 00:13:34,160
Also, I missed you.

209
00:13:59,840 --> 00:14:03,790
So what were you watching when I walked in?

210
00:14:04,850 --> 00:14:06,690
The TV series you were in.

211
00:14:07,390 --> 00:14:08,750
You look amazing in them.

212
00:14:08,750 --> 00:14:11,820
Right? Don't I give off a unique vibe?

213
00:14:12,220 --> 00:14:15,220
I know I'm not a master at acting,

214
00:14:15,290 --> 00:14:17,510
but my acting isn't all that bad either.

215
00:14:17,930 --> 00:14:18,980
That's right.

216
00:14:19,030 --> 00:14:22,030
Even if you see those comments,
there's no need to feel discouraged.

217
00:14:22,230 --> 00:14:24,750
- Since they aren't true at all.
- I can't agree more.

218
00:14:25,240 --> 00:14:26,870
If you see those types
of comments from now on,

219
00:14:28,340 --> 00:14:29,570
press the thumbs down button.

220
00:14:30,140 --> 00:14:31,200
Okay.

221
00:14:36,210 --> 00:14:37,610
Why are you looking at me like that?

222
00:14:40,020 --> 00:14:41,550
I wonder how much you were hurt...

223
00:14:42,220 --> 00:14:44,260
in order to become this composed.

224
00:14:47,530 --> 00:14:49,300
I know you went through some hard times.

225
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:53,400
I feel happy that you overcame it.

226
00:15:17,520 --> 00:15:20,580
Ms. Oh. Mr. Kwon didn't
come back yet, right?

227
00:15:21,260 --> 00:15:22,930
Join us for lunch then.

228
00:15:23,130 --> 00:15:25,750
Oh, well...

229
00:15:27,900 --> 00:15:29,670
I'll just wait and have lunch with him.

230
00:15:29,770 --> 00:15:31,480
He'll be back pretty soon.

231
00:15:32,040 --> 00:15:35,310
If I say I ate alone,
he might think I'm disloyal.

232
00:15:36,210 --> 00:15:38,310
All right then. Enjoy your lunch.

233
00:15:38,310 --> 00:15:40,220
You too, Ms. Yang.

234
00:15:47,350 --> 00:15:49,360
When is Mr. Kwon coming back?

235
00:15:53,820 --> 00:15:55,630
These dumplings really taste amazing.

236
00:15:58,030 --> 00:16:01,700
Mr. Yeon, you spattered
hot stew on my face.

237
00:16:03,130 --> 00:16:05,640
From now on, I think we should
exclude hot stews like this...

238
00:16:05,640 --> 00:16:07,480
from our lunch menu.

239
00:16:08,110 --> 00:16:10,440
What if I suffer a burn
on my handsome face...

240
00:16:10,440 --> 00:16:12,780
just because of a pot of dumpling stew?

241
00:16:12,780 --> 00:16:16,320
That's what you call,
"Penny wise and pound foolish."

242
00:16:16,450 --> 00:16:18,620
Penny wise and pound foolish my foot.

243
00:16:19,080 --> 00:16:21,370
Ms. Dan, are you going to
put up with this nonsense?

244
00:16:21,520 --> 00:16:22,720
- Say something.
- What?

245
00:16:23,350 --> 00:16:25,020
- Me?
- Yes.

246
00:16:25,020 --> 00:16:26,960
I know you loathe Mr. Choi.

247
00:16:26,990 --> 00:16:29,790
So don't hold back and
criticize him all you want.

248
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:36,270
When did I say I loathed him?

249
00:16:42,040 --> 00:16:45,070
I think you should stop eating dumplings.

250
00:16:46,010 --> 00:16:49,210
There is a total of 8 dumplings,
and we should each have 2.

251
00:16:49,210 --> 00:16:51,500
But you've already had your share.

252
00:16:51,680 --> 00:16:53,580
Why are you being so cheap over a dumpling?

253
00:16:53,580 --> 00:16:55,390
We can just order more.

254
00:16:55,390 --> 00:16:56,550
Shall we order more then?

255
00:16:56,950 --> 00:16:59,370
But it might take time for
them to cook new dumplings.

256
00:17:00,690 --> 00:17:02,290
We don't have time to wait.

257
00:17:03,330 --> 00:17:05,240
